  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The stapled transanal rectal resection (STARR procedure) is an effective treatment for
      obstructed defecation syndrome (ODS) caused by intussusception and rectocele. Recently a new
      technique has been developed using the new Contour速 TranstarTM stapler, which was
      specifically designed to facilitate the STARR procedure. The investigators would like to
      evaluate the morbidity and quality of life.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
